<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOVAK ON AMERICANS MOVING UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Novak instructs us to quit "bashing the rich" since "most people got richer" 
last decade. 
</P>
<P>
I couldn't agree more that we should "cut the hypocrisy." 
</P>
<P>
Since The Times reported July 24 that the richest 1% of Americans got 87% 
richer last decade while the poorest 20% got 5% poorer (making the widest 
rich-poor gap in 40 years), I suggest we do a lot more than bash the rich and 
the political system that supports them. Let's cut the hypocrisy and find a way 
to disenfranchise the selfish rats so that our country can care for its 
desperate needs. Then they can "put up or shut up." 
</P>
<P>
CAROL BENSON HOLST 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 
</P>
</TEXT>
