</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So Dave Stewart claims that his is still the better team. 
</P>
<P>
Well, I want to thank Dave for clearing things up for me. I was under the 
misconception that teams like the A's, Reds and Yankees of the '70s were great 
teams simply because they consecutively won World (Series) championships. But 
now, Dave, I'll have to change my view. You've made it obvious that winning 
isn't the indicator of true greatness, but rather how often a team gets into a 
position to win a championship. 
</P>
