<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Airlines: Two carriers blamed higher fuel costs for losses in the third 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Chicago-based Midway Airlines Inc. said it lost $18.7 million, compared to a 
$1.9-million loss in the same period a year ago. Revenue rose 37% to $166.6 
million. Phoenix-based America West Airlines said it lost $21.9 million, 
contrasted with a profit of $5.8 million in the same period last year. Revenue 
rose 39% to $338.7 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
