<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON CAMPUS : PIERCE COLLEGE; 
</P>
<P>
STUDENT JOURNALISTS TO COMPETE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 400 student journalists representing 29 colleges from Southern 
California and Arizona are expected to compete for awards at the annual 
Journalism Assn. of Community Colleges regional conference today at Pierce 
College. 
</P>
<P>
The event coincides with the college's annual Harvest Festival, which will be 
the subject of the feature photograph competition. 
</P>
<P>
Feature writers will write about the Pierce College swap meet. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. Customs inspectors will hold a news conference for news writers and 
demonstrate an equipment and dog handling for news photographers. 
</P>
<P>
A golf demonstration is scheduled in the sports photography contest, and a mock 
news conference will be held for sports writers. 
</P>
<P>
The subject of the editorial writing and cartooning competition will be a video 
titled "Faces of the Enemy." 
</P>
</TEXT>
