<HEADLINE>
<P>
BELOVSKY, REMMEL RALLY ORANGE PAST WINLESS FOOTHILL, 12-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARGIE LUCK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUSTIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Foothill High School scored first but failed to score again, remaining winless 
as it fell to Orange, 12-7, Friday night at Tustin High School. 
</P>
<P>
Foothill's Sean Saunders broke free and ran 56 yards to put the Knights on the 
scoreboard early in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Keo Powell kicked the extra point. 
</P>
<P>
But Orange fought back, with quarterback Josh Belovsky running 37 yards for a 
touchdown late in the first quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Remmel put Orange in front in the second quarter when he ran 25 yards for 
a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Foothill quarterback Tim Chaix was sacked three times by the Panther defense, 
and threw an interception with two minutes left to play. 
</P>
<P>
Belovsky completed seven of 13 passes for 65 yards and Remmel gained 60 yards 
in 16 carries to pace Orange (4-3-1 overall, 1-1-1 in Century League play), 
while Foothill (0-7, 0-2) was led by Saunders' 117 yards in 15 carries. MARGIE 
LUCK 
</P>
</TEXT>
