<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER WINS ON LAST-SECOND PASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Backup quarterback Kirk Pierce connected on a 51-yard desperation pass to 
Enrique Gonzalez with two seconds left to give Westminster High School a 23-17 
victory over Huntington Beach in a Sunset League game Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach (5-3, 2-3) had taken the lead 51 seconds earlier when senior 
Alex Acocello hit a 22-yard field goal. 
</P>
<P>
The Lions (3-4-1, 2-1-1) took the kickoff and moved to their own 49. Then 
Pierce entered the game. 
</P>
<P>
With 10 seconds left, Pierce threw an incompletion, but with two seconds left, 
he connected with Gonzalez in the right corner of the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
Westminster led, 10-7, at halftime. The Lions' Lucas Jones ran 13 yards for a 
touchdown with 10:10 left in the second quarter, and Ken Scott kicked a 37-yard 
field goal. 
</P>
<P>
The Oilers scored on a 20-yard pass from Mike Chavira to Gabe Stupin. 
</P>
<P>
Gabe Houston's one-yard run put Huntington Beach up, 14-10. 
</P>
<P>
With 6:37 left, Vance Senteno ran for six yards to put Westminster back in 
front, 16-14. The PAT failed after a bad snap. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach took the ensuing kickoff and kept the ball for almost five 
minutes before Acocello's field goal. HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
