<HEADLINE>
<P>
LUEVANOS LEADS BREA-OLINDA PAST MAGNOLIA, 21-14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jason Luevanos of Brea-Olinda High School threw for 196 yards to lead the 
Wildcats to a 21-14 victory over Magnolia in an Orange League football game 
Friday night at Glover Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Brea held Magnolia to 57 yards total offense. 
</P>
<P>
Luevanos completed 13 of 18 passing attempts including a seven-yard scoring 
pass to Jamie Baraglia to give Brea a 6-0 lead early in the second quarter. 
Brea (5-2-1, 2-0) scored again when Luevanos scored on a six-yard run with 1:55 
left in the half. Baraglia ran for the two-point conversion and the Wildcats 
led, 14-0, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
Magnolia cut the lead to 14-7 on a three-yard run by Ariel Courvetier with 8:52 
left in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Brea came back to take a 21-7 lead when Lew Morales scored on a three-yard run 
with 10:48 left in the game. KEN HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
