FOURTH-QUARTER BURST PROPELS LA QUINTA TO 43-14 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Quinta High School broke open a tight Garden Grove League game by scoring 
four fourth-quarter touchdowns to remain undefeated with a 43-14 homecoming 
victory over host Bolsa Grande Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Leading, 15-14, with 10 minutes remaining, the Aztecs (8-0, 5-0 in league) got 
the break they needed when Don Hopkins recovered a Matador fumble on the Bolsa 
Grande 17-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
Three plays later, Hopkins hit halfback Walter Dawkins with a 21-yard scoring 
pass with 9:06 remaining for a 21-14 Aztec lead. 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande (2-6, 1-4) stayed close until failing on a fourth-down play on its 
own 24-yard line with 5:22 remaining to set up Hopkins' 10-yard scoring pass to 
Justin Sogoian with 3:07 left. The Aztecs turned the game into a route with 
pass interception returns of 51 yards by George Sanchez and 45 yards by Dawkins 
for late scores. 
</P>
<P>
For Bolsa Grande, Maurice Wilson ran for 134 yards and one touchdown in 18 
carries and Marcus Wilson added 88 yards and another touchdown in 23 carries. 
Hopkins led the La Quinta offense with 14 pass completions in 22 attempts for 
two touchdowns. TOM BIRSCHBACH 
