DANA POINT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rob Johnson threw three touchdown passes to lead No. 1-ranked El Toro to a 33-6 
victory over Dana Hills in a South Coast League game at Dana Hills Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
El Toro (8-0, 3-0 in league) scored 21 consecutive points in the fourth quarter 
after Dana Hills (3-4-1, 0-3) surprised the Chargers by trailing by just 12-6 
after three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
Two of Johnson's touchdown passes were in the fourth quarter. The first went to 
Bret Sanders for 30 yards, and the second went to Wade Jackson for 26 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson completed 15 of 21 passes for 192 yards and threw one interception. 
</P>
<P>
Sanders was the game's leading rusher with 93 yards in 16 carries and one 
touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
The Chargers drove 66 yards for the game's first touchdown midway through the 
second quarter. Brad Hulse caught a 17-yard pass from Johnson for the score. 
Shaun Coleman blocked the extra-point attempt. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills then drove from its own 20 to the El Toro eight before settling for 
a 21-yard field goal by John Ashley to make it 6-3 with 1 minute 30 seconds 
left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
But El Toro's James Rios returned the ensuing kickoff 52 yards to the Dana 
Hills 35, and following a 24-yard pass from Johnson to Jackson, Sanders scored 
from the one. 
</P>
