<HEADLINE>
<P>
OAK TREE; 
</P>
<P>
TODAY'S CARD A MARATHON SESSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB MIESZERSKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today isn't a day for faint-hearted horseplayers at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
There will be 14 races on which to wager, beginning with the seven Breeders' 
Cup events at 10:55 a.m. After the Breeders' Cup Classic, there will be seven 
races run locally. 
</P>
<P>
The feature, which will be run as the 13th race, is the $84,600 Morvich 
Handicap at 6 1/2 furlongs on the turf. 
</P>
<P>
Oraibi is the probable favorite in the Morvich, which has attracted 10 other 
starters. 
</P>
<P>
Third in the Legend's Last Ride in February, Oraibi was injured in the race and 
went to stud for a time at agent Tony Matos' farm in Llano. Oraibi, trained by 
Richard Mandella, has won six of his 18 starts, but only one of his victories 
has been on the turf. 
</P>
<P>
Still, he has never been worse than third on the grass and he was second to 
Shirkee in his comeback two weeks ago on the course. Julio Garcia will ride 
Oraibi, who is the high weight at 118 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
Other probable contenders in the Morvich include Frost Free, Snipledo, Robyn 
Dancer, Doyouseewhatisee and Sam Who. 
</P>
<P>
The beaten favorite in the Budweiser Breeders' Cup Handicap at Bay Meadows last 
month, Frost Free will be looking for his second victory in three turf starts 
for trainer John Sadler. The gelded son of It's Freezing worked six furlongs in 
1:12 4/5 Sunday and Jorge Velasquez has the mount. 
</P>
<P>
Snipledo's six-race winning streak ended when he ran fifth in the Ancient Title 
Handicap and he will be making his grass debut. Robyn Dancer is a late threat 
who was fourth behind Oraibi two Saturdays ago, Doyouseewhatisee handled a 
lesser field on the layout Oct. 4 and Sam Who is trying to remember how he used 
to do it. A starter in the Breeders' Cup Sprint last year, he is winless in 
seven 1990 starts and has been the beaten choice four times. 
</P>
<P>
Others scheduled to go include Go On In, Gallant Sailor, Yes I'm Blue, Sulaymi 
and Waterscape. 
</P>
<P>
Stylish Star, who won the Autumn Days Handicap on opening day, heads a field of 
12 fillies and mares in Sunday's $114,600 Louis R. Rowan Handicap at a mile on 
the turf. 
</P>
<P>
Stylish Star, a four-year-old, ended a six-race losing streak with her 
come-from-behind victory in the Autumn Days. Her last two successes have been 
at 6 1/2 furlongs, but she has won around two turns. Eddie Delahoussaye rides 
for trainer Dan Hendricks. 
</P>
<P>
Oeilladine, who didn't have clear sailing when third behind Sweet Roberta and 
Brown Bess in the California Jockey Club at Bay Meadows three weeks ago, is the 
filly to beat. She has won two of four starts on the Santa Anita grass and is 
reunited with Gary Stevens, who was aboard for both of those victories. 
</P>
<P>
The other Rowan entrants are Baba Cool, who won the race last year, Polar Bird, 
Estrella Fuega, Mystical Lass, Petalia, Spectacular Face, Kikala, Something 
Comfy, Chispa Brava and Island Jamboree. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Horse Racing Notes 
</P>
<P>
Gates will open at 8 a.m. at Santa Anita. . . . Favored Sexy Slew easily won 
the $61,250 Dark Star Handicap Friday at Santa Anita. Ridden by Kent Desormeaux 
and trained by David Hofmans, she defeated Tis Juliet and four other fillies 
and mares, covering the seven furlongs in 1:21 2/5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
