<HEADLINE>
<P>
I'M SKY HIGH WINS STUYVESANT HANDICAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ELMONT, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I'm Sky High took the lead entering the stretch and went on to a three-length 
victory Friday in the $119,600 Stuyvesant Handicap at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
The winner carried 111 pounds, including jockey Mike Smith, in the race for 
3-year-olds andup. 
</P>
<P>
Silver Survivor was second in the seven-horse field, 1 1/2 lengths ahead of 
Lost Opportunity. 
</P>
<P>
I'm Sky High covered 1 1/8 miles on the fast track in 1:48 1/5 to earn $71,760 
with his fifth victory in twelve starts this year. 
</P>
<P>
I'm Sky High returned $7.40, $4.00 and $2.80. Silver Survivor paid $5.20 and 
$3.20. Lost Opportunity was $3.40 to show. 
</P>
