<HEADLINE>
<P>
4 ARRESTED IN KIDNAP, GANG-RAPE OF WOMAN; 
</P>
<P>
CRIME: SAN FRANCISCO WOMAN WAS ABDUCTED AS SHE WALKED TO BUY FORMULA FOR HER 
BABY, AUTHORITIES SAY. ONE SUSPECT IS A SCHOOL SECURITY GUARD. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILKINSON, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Long Beach school security officer and three other men were arrested Friday 
in the kidnaping and gang-rape of a San Francisco woman who was abducted as she 
walked to buy formula for her baby, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old woman, visiting the Los Angeles area with her husband and 
child, was intercepted on her way to a store early Friday morning, forced into 
a car and driven several blocks to where she was raped, Sheriff's Sgt. Bob 
Olmsted said. 
</P>
<P>
After an hourlong ordeal, she was rescued by two sheriff's deputies who 
happened onto the scene, Olmsted said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies assigned to patrol the Metro Rail Blue Line spotted the car -- its 
license plate covered with tape and plastic bags -- and approached two men 
standing alongside it. As the two men started to walk away, deputies saw a gun 
tucked into one man's waistband. 
</P>
<P>
The two men were detained and when the deputies reached the car, they found 
another man holding a semiautomatic pistol to the woman's head in the back 
seat. A fourth man was sitting in the front seat, Olmsted said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect in the back seat was identified as Victor Lopez Jr., 27, a security 
officer for the Long Beach school system and a reserve-duty Los Angeles County 
Parks and Recreation safety officer. The three other men were identified as 
gang members. 
</P>
<P>
Olmsted said the woman was apparently abducted near the intersection of Martin 
Luther King Jr. Boulevard and Pacific Coast Highway about 1 a.m. The men drove 
her to the 1300 block of Lime Avenue, a row of commercial buildings and 
residences near Polytechnic High School, where Lopez was waiting. 
</P>
<P>
The car and both guns were registered to Lopez, authorities said. One of the 
guns -- a 9-millimeter Beretta -- was Lopez's county-issued weapon. 
</P>
<P>
All four men were booked at the Carson sheriff's station on suspicion of rape, 
conspiracy to commit rape, sodomy, forced oral copulation and assault with a 
deadly weapon. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez's boss said he was shocked at the allegations and described Lopez as a 
reliable employee who never caused trouble. 
</P>
<P>
"He's been a dependable officer," said Joe Romero, chief of security for the 
Long Beach school system. "He's real quiet and just goes about and does his 
job." 
</P>
<P>
He said Lopez had worked for Long Beach for 2 1/2 years. Lopez is single and 
lives with his mother in Burbank, Romero said. 
</P>
<P>
As a school security officer, Lopez's duties included responding to fire or 
burglary alarms at any of Long Beach's schools. He was not on duty at the time 
of the alleged kidnaping and rape. 
</P>
<P>
The other suspects arrested with Lopez were identified by authorities as Oniva 
David Tautolo, 21; Owen Fuimaono Jr., 22, and Lau Talo Jr., 22, all of Long 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez was being held in lieu of $50,000 bail, while bail was set at $30,000 for 
the others. 
</P>
<P>
The woman, whose name was not released, was treated at a local hospital. She, 
her husband and their child had been staying at a Long Beach motel for several 
weeks while visiting relatives in Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
KIDNAPINGS -- LOS ANGLES COUNTY; RAPE -- LOS ANGELES COUNTY; SCHOOL EMPLOYEES; 
SECURITY GUARDS; GANGS -- LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
