<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GOLDEN LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM PERERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quartz Hill 35, Ridgecrest Burroughs 7 -- Erik Thomas gained 169 yards in 14 
carries, including touchdown runs of 80 and 17 yards, to lead the Rebels at 
home. Selves Smith added 131 yards in 13 carries, David Nelson gained 42 yards 
in nine carries and each scored a touchdown as Quartz Hill (6-2, 3-0) piled up 
342 rushing yards. 
</P>
<P>
Quartz Hill defensive back Joel Hansen set a school record with a 93-yard 
interception return for a touchdown in the third quarter. TIM PERERA 
</P>
