<TEXT>
<P>
Saugus 17, Antelope Valley 15 -- Rob Chilton kicked a 25-yard field goal midway 
through the final period and Saugus held on for the victory at home. 
</P>
<P>
Saugus scored on its first possession when quarterback Jason Bobby capped an 
80-yard drive with a four-yard touchdown run. The Antelopes answered quickly 
when Freddie Edwards dashed 55 yards for a touchdown and then ran in the 
two-point conversion. 
</P>
<P>
The Centurions regained the lead for good in the third quarter as David Doyle 
plunged two yards for a touchdown. After Chilton's field goal, Antelope Valley 
cut the deficit to two points with 1:30 left on Mike Fossati's one-yard sneak 
and the conversion. KEVIN ASSEO 
