By MICHAEL ARKUSH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Channel Islands 13, Agoura 10 -- An inspired Channel Islands defense stopped 
Agoura running back Kurt Klotz on the one-foot line with one minute to play, 
preserving a victory at Agoura. 
</P>
<P>
With five minutes to play, Agoura drove from its 31 to the Channel Islands' 
five and seemed ready to seize the lead. 
</P>
<P>
But three consecutive running plays only moved the ball to the one, setting up 
the final attempt. 
</P>
<P>
Lamont Pearson dashed 79 yards for the Raiders' go-ahead touchdown late in the 
third quarter. Pearson finished with 106 yards in 11 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura (5-3, 2-3) took a 10-7 lead with 3:51 to play in the first half on a 
nine-yard run by quarterback Sean Fitzgerald, who completed 11 of 19 for 173 
yards. MICHAEL ARKUSH 
