<P>
In another Northwest Valley Conference game: 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 24, Cleveland 20 -- Chatsworth chalked up its first league victory 
behind the running of tailback Rayna Stewart, who rushed for a game-high 126 
yards in 18 carries. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Brandon Ruedy completed five of 13 passes for 59 yards and two 
touchdowns for Chatsworth (2-4, 1-3). 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland quarterback David Erhardt returned after missing two games because of 
a separated shoulder. He completed 14 of 24 for 179 yards and one touchdown, 
and also scored on a one-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
Erhardt couldn't overcome the Cavaliers' mistakes, however. Cleveland was 
penalized 14 times for 163 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Cleveland (0-5-1, 0-4) trailed, 14-0, in the first quarter when Erhardt entered 
the game. The Cavaliers were forced to punt on that possession, but they scored 
on the ensuing one, capped by Erhardt's one-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
Ibn Bilal gained 83 yards in 12 carries for Cleveland, and caught two passes 
for 20 yards and a touchdown -- a 21-yarder with 2:21 left. STEVE WILLIAMS 
