<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paul Tagliabue, NFL commissioner, notified the two ownership groups of the 
Minnesota Vikings that he will evaluate and resolve significant aspects of 
their dispute. 
</P>
<P>
Banker Carl Pohlad, who also owns the Minnesota Twins, and businessman Irwin 
Jacobs own one-third of the Vikings' voting stock and want to gain control of 
the team. They are suing General Manager Mike Lynn and the majority 
stockholders over the method in which Lynn gained control. 
</P>
