PAPER SAYS 911 OPERATOR IGNORED CALL ON BEATING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An emergency operator told a 7-year-old girl to "get off the phone" when the 
child called to report that her brother was being beaten, a newspaper reported 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Troy and Jane McCants pleaded guilty Thursday to involuntary manslaughter in 
the June death of their 6-year-old son, Antwon Dumas. Records showed that their 
daughter's 911 emergency call was ignored, the Detroit News said. 
</P>
<P>
Jane McCants called for an ambulance five minutes later, according to the tape, 
but the boy was dead when the ambulance arrived. 
</P>
<P>
The Wayne County prosecutor said the operator has been disciplined but would 
not disclose what measures were taken. 
</P>
