<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; 
</P>
<P>
CHAMBER TO SPONSOR HARVEST FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chamber of Commerce will sponsor a Harvest Festival on Sunday, featuring a 
pumpkin patch and hayrides. 
</P>
<P>
The festival, to herald the coming of fall, will take place from 10 a.m. to 4 
p.m. at the historical Jones Family Mini Farm, 31791 Los Rios St. Admission is 
free. 
</P>
<P>
Pumpkin-decorating contests, divided into three age groups for children, will 
start at noon, 2 p.m. and 3 p.m. All tools for decorating will be provided and 
prizes will be awarded by Capistrano Gardens Nursery. 
</P>
<P>
The pumpkins will be offered for sale, with proceeds going to the Chamber of 
Commerce. 
</P>
<P>
Local schools will have game booths. Entertainment and food will also be 
available. 
</P>
<P>
Children may visit with farm animals, take a hayride or ride a pony. 
</P>
<P>
Officials said visitors should park downtown and walk to Los Rios Street. MARY 
ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
