<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPECIAL SCREENINGS TO SALUTE 12-YEAR 'ROCKY' TIME WARP; 
</P>
<P>
MOVIE: AMATEURS WILL THROW A BIRTHDAY/HALLOWEEN BASH AT THE BALBOA FOR 
FRANK-N-FURTER ET AL. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KENNETH WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When it opened in October of 1975, "The Rocky Horror Picture Show" was met with 
about as much enthusiasm as Ozzy Osbourne at a church revival. But over the 
years, its growth in popularity has made it the granddaddy of midnight movies, 
a standard-bearer among cult films. 
</P>
<P>
In acknowledgment of this triumph and to celebrate 12 years locally of midnight 
rendezvous with Frank-n-Furter, Riff Raff and the rest of the "Rocky" gang, 
Midnight Insanity, a local troupe of amateur actors and "Rocky" enthusiasts, is 
presenting special anniversary and Halloween screenings of the movie tonight 
and Wednesday at the Balboa Landmark Theatre, 709 E. Balboa Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
There'll be birthday cake tonight and balloons and costume contests both 
nights. Prizes include a CD soundtrack from the film, posters and buttons, and 
tapes of "Rocky" radio spots, and renditions of "Rocky" songs from a variety of 
live theater productions. 
</P>
<P>
Tonight's party starts at 11:30, with the screening itself scheduled for 12:45. 
Wednesday's times are 11 and 11:45. Admission each night is $6. Information: 
(714) 675-3570. KENNETH WILLIAMS 
</P>
</TEXT>
